{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"scope","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/scope","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"\n<ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/background_color\">background_color</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/categories\">categories</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/description\">description</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/display\">display</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/display_override\">display_override</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/icons\">icons</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/name\">name</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/orientation\">orientation</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/prefer_related_applications\">prefer_related_applications</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/protocol_handlers\">protocol_handlers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/related_applications\">related_applications</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/scope\">scope</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/screenshots\">screenshots</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/share_target\">share_target</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/short_name\">short_name</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/shortcuts\">shortcuts</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/start_url\">start_url</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/theme_color\">theme_color</a></li></ol>\n","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"properties\">\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"row\">Type</th>\n      <td><code>String</code></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"row\">Mandatory</th>\n      <td>No</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n<p>The <code>scope</code> member is a string that defines the navigation scope of this web application's application context. It restricts what web pages can be viewed while the manifest is applied. If the user navigates outside the scope, it reverts to a normal web page inside a browser tab or window.</p>\n<p>If the <code>scope</code> is a relative URL, the base URL will be the URL of the manifest.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>If the scope is relative, the manifest URL is used as a base URL:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: json notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token property\">\"scope\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"/app/\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The following scope limits navigation to the current site:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: json notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token property\">\"scope\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"https://example.com/\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Finally, the following example limits navigation to a subdirectory of the current site:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: json notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token property\">\"scope\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"https://example.com/subdirectory/\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/manifest/#scope-member","title":"Web Application Manifest"}],"query":"html.manifest.scope"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"html.manifest.scope","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/scope/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The scope member is a string that defines the navigation scope of this web application's application context. It restricts what web pages can be viewed while the manifest is applied. If the user navigates outside the scope, it reverts to a normal web page inside a browser tab or window.","popularity":0.001,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:38:45.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"scope","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"scope","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/manifest/scope","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/manifest/scope/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/f22e42182591e38590c9add80de91a51bce3cde2","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest","title":"Web app manifests"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/scope","title":"scope"}],"pageTitle":"scope - Web app manifests | MDN","noIndexing":false}}